news.title: Country's housing market at higher risk of correction: Bank of Canada
news.para: Paul Beaudry, in a virtual speech to a provincial regulator, also said Canada's main financial system vulnerabilities - housing market imbalances and high levels of household debt - had been intensified by the pandemic.

news.title: ITC Hotel goes aggressive in new properties rollout
news.para: ​ITC Hotels is pursuing an 'asset right' strategy while simultaneously leveraging ITC's world class properties to drive growth, the official said.

news.title: Virtual real estate plot sells for record $2.4 million
news.para: Decentraland is an online environment - also called a "metaverse" - where users can buy land, visit buildings, walk around and meet people as avatars.

news.title: Austrian central bank sees growing risks from mortgages amid property boom
news.para: In its last semi-annual Financial Stability Report in June, the Austrian National Bank (ONB) said closer scrutiny of mortgage lending was called for to ward off any systemic risk, and ONB officials said they would take a wait-and-see approach.

news.title: Gurugram: 1,500 illegal structures razed, three-acre land cleared along Golf Course Road
news.para: The HSVP is yet to clear another 4-acre land at this location. The authority, according to an official, is planning to carry a two-day long drive starting Wednesday to remove squatters from this area.

news.title: IHCL to manage four more Ambuja Neotia properties
news.para: ​Chairman of Ambuja Neotia group Harsh Neotia said the properties will be under the Taj brand, two of which are in New Town, one each in Patna and Gangtok.

news.title: Chinese city of Chengdu to ensure cash-strapped developers get funds
news.para: Real estate firms face a financial crunch due to regulatory curbs on borrowing, with China Evergrande Group at the centre of a crisis which has involved offshore debt defaults, credit rating downgrades and the dumping of shares and bonds.

news.title: Residents of DLF-1 want Gurugram civic body to set up waste processing unit
news.para: The online petition has collected over 200 signatures. Although many residents have adopted waste segregation at source, further management has become a problem in the absence of separate collection, they claimed.

news.title: ByteDance plans to spin off real estate listing business
news.para: Xingfuli was set up in 2018, joining the many apps ByteDance operates alongside Douyin, the Chinese equivalent of TikTok, news aggregator Toutiao and others.

news.title: Thane: Mhada now plans to make Kalwa affordable housing hub
news.para: Jitendra Awhad said the department was working out a plan to procure a disputed land belonging to a now defunct engineering company spread over 100 acres in Kalwa (east).

news.title: Construction of 3.61 lakh houses under PMAY-Urban approved
news.para: At the CSMC meeting, an e-Finance module was also launched by the housing secretary. The e-Finance module has been integrated with all modules of the PMAY-Urban MIS system.

news.title: More irregularities tumble out of Bengaluru development body as raids resume
news.para: On Tuesday, the zonal offices at RT Nagar, Banashankari, Vijayanagar, and HSR Layout were raided. Innumerable documents were scanned and the raids are likely to continue for another couple of days, sources said.

news.title: IT department detects Rs 400 crore black income after raids on two NCR realtors
news.para: The Central Board of Direct Taxes (CBDT) said in a statement that the preliminary analysis of the seized data found that the groups were receiving part of the sale consideration in cash against the sale of flats and such cash is not recorded in the books of accounts.

news.title: Reserve Bank of New Zealand hikes rates again, warns homeowners to get ready for more
news.para: The Reserve Bank of New Zealand (RBNZ) lifted the official cash rate (OCR) a quarter of a percentage point to 0.75% in the final policy meeting of the year, as the country shakes off its pandemic slump and prepares to reopen to the world.

news.title: Gaya civic body to install QR code in 70,000 houses
news.para: The GMC has recently secured top position among all urban local bodies in the state having population of less than 10 lakh in Swachh Survekshan 2021.
